1 A JOINT RESOLUTION directing the establishment of the Gun Violence
2 Prevention Task Force.
3 WHEREAS, gun violence is an epidemic plaguing every state in the country; and
4 WHEREAS, the Congress of the United States passed the Bipartisan Safer
5 Communities Act in 2022 in an effort to reduce gun crime; and
6 WHEREAS, both Democrats and Republicans, including Senate Minority Leader
7 Mitch McConnell, supported the Bipartisan Safer Communities Act, demonstrating that
8 preventing gun violence is an area where legislators can reach a bipartisan consensus; and
9 WHEREAS, Kentucky has one of the nation's highest rates of gun violence; and
10 WHEREAS, the rate of gun deaths in Kentucky has increased 38 percent from 2013
11 to 2022, with 826 Kentuckians dying from gun violence in an average year; and
12 WHEREAS, the General Assembly recognizes that gun violence is a serious
13 problem in Kentucky, as evidenced by the passage of House Bill 5 and Senate Bill 20
14 during the 2024 Regular Session; and
15 WHEREAS, the General Assembly has a sacred obligation to ensure that citizens of
16 the Commonwealth can live in peace and freedom, which includes the freedom to live
17 without fear of gun violence; and
18 WHEREAS, the General Assembly can accomplish that goal without interfering
19 with the right of law-abiding citizens to keep and bear arms;
20 NOW, THEREFORE,
21 Be it resolved by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
22 Section 1. The Legislative Research Commission is hereby directed to create
23 the Gun Violence Prevention Task Force to study the causes of gun violence and to
24 examine ways to prevent gun violence in the Commonwealth of Kentucky. The Gun
25 Violence Prevention Task Force shall:
26 (1) Study the causes and contributing factors to gun violence in the
27 Commonwealth of Kentucky;
