1 (2) Review data on both fatal and nonfatal gun-related incidents in Kentucky;
2 (3) Collect data to examine the impact of gun violence on the Medicaid budget;
3 (4) Examine existing laws in the Commonwealth that address the issue of gun
4 violence and assess their effectiveness;
5 (5) Review studies and legislative action by other states and the federal
6 government on the causes and costs of gun violence;
7 (6) Identify existing resources to prevent gun violence;
8 (7) Recommend new laws, or changes to existing law, to reduce the rate of gun
9 violence; and
10 (8) Take any other action the task force deems necessary to study the issue of gun
11 violence in the Commonwealth.
12 Section 2. The Gun Violence Prevention Task Force shall be composed of the
13 following members, with final membership of the task force being subject to the
14 consideration and approval of the Legislative Research Commission:
15 (1) Three members of the House of Representatives, including two members
16 appointed by the Speaker of the House of Representatives, one of whom shall be
17 designated to serve as co-chair, and one member of the minority party in the House of
18 Representatives appointed by the Minority Floor Leader in the House of Representatives;
19 (2) Three members of the Senate, including two members appointed by the
20 President of the Senate, one of whom shall be designated to serve as co-chair, and one
21 member of the minority party in the Senate appointed by the Minority Floor Leader in the
22 Senate;
23 (3) The secretary of the Justice and Public Safety Cabinet;
24 (4) The commissioner of the Department of Kentucky State Police;
25 (5) The commissioner of the Department of Juvenile Justice;
26 (6) The commissioner of the Department for Behavioral Health, Developmental
27 and Intellectual Disabilities;
