1 (7) One representative from the Department for Medicaid Services;
2 (8) The commissioner of the Department for Public Health;
3 (9) The public advocate; and
4 (10) Ten members to be appointed by the Legislative Research Commission as
5 follows:
6 (a) One member representing research or educational institutions that study gun
7 violence;
8 (b) One member representing the Kentucky Center for School Safety;
9 (c) One member representing hospitals and the medical field;
10 (d) One member representing owners of gun stores;
11 (e) One member representing community- or faith-based organizations;
12 (f) One licensed clinical social worker who has experience in suicide prevention;
13 (g) One member representing victims of gun violence;
14 (h) One member representing survivors of domestic violence and abuse;
15 (i) One member of the Commonwealth's Attorneys Association from a list of
16 three nominees recommended by the Attorney General; and
17 (j) One member representing law enforcement.
18 Section 3. The Gun Violence Prevention Task Force shall meet at least once per
19 month during the 2025 Interim of the General Assembly and shall submit its findings,
20 legislative recommendations, or a memorandum to the Legislative Research Commission
21 no later than December 1, 2025. If legislative recommendations are submitted, the
22 Legislative Research Commission may refer the recommendations to the appropriate
23 committee or committees of jurisdiction in advance of the 2026 Regular Session of the
24 General Assembly.
25 Section 4. Provisions of this Resolution to the contrary notwithstanding, the
26 Legislative Research Commission shall have the authority to alternatively assign the
27 issues identified herein to an interim joint committee or subcommittee thereof, and to
